<title type="html"><![CDATA[Noise channel single sound?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6287&amp;p=59928#p59928"><![CDATA[
I generally use this as a reference:  <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://slack.net/~ant/nes-emu/apu_ref.txt">http://slack.net/~ant/nes-emu/apu_ref.txt</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Next is, well.....How do I make it decrease without it repeating?<br /></div><br /><br />- disable looping (bit 5 clear)<br />- enable decay (bit 4 clear)<br /><br />The side effect of this is that the length counter will be enabled, so you'll have to specify a longer length or else the note will cut out early.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">LDA #%0000xxxx ; where xxxx is the decay speed<br />      ; higher values = slower decay<br />STA $400C<br /><br />LDA #%00000111<br />STA $400E<br /><br />lda #%00001000  ; use the longest length to prevent the note from cutting out<br />STA $400F<br /></div><br /><br /><br />Or... you can just use a constant note like you were before and just change the volume every couple of frames.<br /><br />EDIT:  doh too slow<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Sat Apr 10, 2010 12:47 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
