<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6287&amp;p=59926#p59926</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6287&amp;p=59926#p59926"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Noise channel single sound?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6287&amp;p=59926#p59926"><![CDATA[
To get a non-looping envelope, you need to turn off bits 5 and 4 of $400C and load a valid length counter value into bits 7-3 of $400F. But at that point, a more versatile way involves software envelopes: turn on bits 5 and 4 for constant-volume mode, and write decreasing values to bits 3-0 over the course of several frames.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Apr 10, 2010 12:44 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
